GF Zucchini Penne with Lentil-balls 😁 This year we are staying away from the processed fake meat as much as possible. #Plantbased #NotaChef 
.
About the meal: I’m getting protein and fiber from the PASTA (choose healthy flours that come from plants/seeds/legumes) AND the lentil balls. Cooked veggies are great, but adding some raw veggies on top always changes the game. Your body will thank you. There are also portobello bits in the sauce and mushrooms are good for the brain. Ideally, blend tomatoes and seasonings from scratch for your sauce :). The oils you use also matter. Most restaurants use canola and other unhealthy seed oils.
.
I still like to eat out sometimes, but awareness is key.
.
 Remember it’s not about being perfect, it’s about making progress. ❤️

Edible Healthier Cookie Dough: 

1/3 cup chickpea flour (I recommend almond flour instead for a better texture and taste but I didn’t have it)
1 cup oat flour 
1 cup raw almond butter
1/3 cup pure maple syrup 
1 tbsp vanilla extract 
Chocolate chips to taste (yes, it’s dairy free)

Get that protein in while you satiate the sweet tooth!

Note: You can use any nut flour (wheat flour is unsafe to eat raw). You can also swap almond butter for any nut butter. If you want to be even healthier, use raw cacao nibs instead of chocolate chips. 

Inspired by #healthygirlkitchen but switched up some ingredients. :)

#plantbased #glutenfree #vegan #ediblecookiedough

Healthy Chickpea Chocolate Chip Cookies! These are delicious, healthy (ish), and energizing ☺️

1 can chickpeas washed and rinsed
1/2 cup raw almond butter
1/3 cup pure maple syrup
2 tbsp vanilla extract
1/4 cup coconut milk
little sea salt (optional)
Blend
1/2 spoon baking powder
1/2 spoon baking soda
Dairy free chocolate chips to taste.. 
Bake at 350 for 20 minutes.

A lot of you have standards, but they are unrealistic until you change. You want someone to be exactly like you: feel/think/love like you do, but they are not you, and you are not them. You lack compassion for differences, but want someone to be compassionate to you. Sometimes you have just as many unappealing qualities as the people you complain about, but you’re not even aware because you haven’t done the inner work to see yourself through another lens and improve your shortcomings. 

You don’t like to compromise, yet you want a relationship or a business that requires a massive load of compromise. Yes, it’s great to have standards, but you gotta make sure you also uphold to a standard with yourself and ask: do you qualify for that standard? How so? Are you constantly working on your mental, physical, and spiritual health? How good are your conflict resolution skills? Why do you feel you are entitled to have what you are demanding? 

In a line up of the best of the best… if you want top tier… are YOU top tier? Be honest. Look in the mirror, uncensored. What are you doing about it?

You’d rather drink, sit and complain that society and people are trash, instead of working on YOU to be able to attract what you want. 

There a lot of wonderful and multifaceted people, places, and things in the world. If you can’t find it, you have to look within.

It starts with you. ❤️

What are your summer body goals?

(Shoulders/upper body training session by @lee23am )

I just heard Mercury is in Gatorade, and folks are complaining again. It’s all love & jokes, but seriously, sometimes ask yourself: are you constantly finding external reasons to make sense of “life sucks”? Are you making excuses instead of working on what you can change? Do you find comfort in blaming something else to avoid accountability?

Life is full of ups and downs, but I can promise you someone is living their best life this whole Gatorade. Why not shift your perspective and decide- today is gonna be a better day? 

Happy Monday loves ❤️
